The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for subspace clustering, which involves learning nonlinear transformations of the data to better fit the subspace assumption. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the use of deep learning for clustering and feature learning.
